{
  "stem": "1502.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We did not make plans to leave, because my father was not financially in a position to move.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because you had to have money to leave.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was no place where to go.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Jews would not be granted entry into any country easily, and they just were just too busy with daily problems to think about moving.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I'm talking the first years-- '33, '34, '35, '36, until 1939.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Only a handful of very wealthy diamond dealers in Antwerp moved to-- to the United States, or to England.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And besides, no one would imagine anything like what's going to happen in the future.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We knew, because in the years from 9-- [BACKGROUND NOISE] --from 1933 until the war, you know, Belgium was a neighboring country with Germany.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we had a-- a flood of Jewish refugees coming from Germany into Belgium, all the time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so we knew of the things that happened in Germany, and we knew the way they carried out pogroms against the Jews.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We knew of the persecution.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But first of all, we never imagined they would come to Belgium.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- and then, we never imagined that they would be out there to exterminate the Jew.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And in the beginning, everybody thought that the Nazis are a temporary thing, that they will be in power two years, or three years, or four years, and then the German people will overthrow them.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because they wouldn't like the way they're handling the-- the government in the country.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So there was no question of making preparation to get out of Belgium.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Things started to deteriorate when the war broke out, when they entered-- the Nazis entered Poland in September, 1939.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the-- France and England declared war on Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But Belgium and Holland declared their neutrality.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
